{
  "video_id": "MQrhPhan5Gw",
  "title": "Why Africa must become a center of knowledge again | Olúfẹ́mi Táíwò",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 13116.0,
      "end_time": 17227.0,
      "text": "What stands between Africa&#39;s current prostrate condition"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 17251.0,
      "end_time": 22880.0,
      "text": "and a future of prosperity and abundance for its long-suffering populations?"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 22912.0,
      "end_time": 24156.0,
      "text": "One word:"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 24725.0,
      "end_time": 25902.0,
      "text": "knowledge."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 26798.0,
      "end_time": 31316.0,
      "text": "If Africa is to become a continent that offers the best life for humans,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 31340.0,
      "end_time": 34298.0,
      "text": "it must become a knowledge society"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 34322.0,
      "end_time": 35590.0,
      "text": "immediately."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 35994.0,
      "end_time": 40697.0,
      "text": "This is what I have called \"Africa&#39;s knowledge imperative.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 41923.0,
      "end_time": 45754.0,
      "text": "Our universities must reduce emphasis on producing manpower"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 45778.0,
      "end_time": 48309.0,
      "text": "for running our civil society,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 48333.0,
      "end_time": 50990.0,
      "text": "our economy"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 50123.0,
      "end_time": 52614.0,
      "text": "and our political institutions."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 53148.0,
      "end_time": 57670.0,
      "text": "They should be dedicated mainly to knowledge production."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 58114.0,
      "end_time": 62440.0,
      "text": "What sense is there in producing civil engineers"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 62680.0,
      "end_time": 65695.0,
      "text": "who are not supported by soil scientists and geologists,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 65719.0,
      "end_time": 70600.0,
      "text": "who make it their business to create knowledge about our soil"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 70310.0,
      "end_time": 71451.0,
      "text": "and our rocks?"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 72417.0,
      "end_time": 75636.0,
      "text": "What use is there in producing lawyers"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 75660.0,
      "end_time": 79180.0,
      "text": "without juries who produce knowledge"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 80447.0,
      "end_time": 84134.0,
      "text": "of the underlying philosophical foundations of the legal system?"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 85642.0,
      "end_time": 87705.0,
      "text": "We must seek knowledge."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 88466.0,
      "end_time": 91532.0,
      "text": "We must approach the matter of knowledge"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 91556.0,
      "end_time": 94420.0,
      "text": "with a maniacal commitment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 94445.0,
      "end_time": 96598.0,
      "text": "without let or hindrance."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 97480.0,
      "end_time": 101159.0,
      "text": "Though we must seek knowledge to solve problems we know of,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 101860.0,
      "end_time": 104116.0,
      "text": "we must also seek knowledge"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 104140.0,
      "end_time": 106116.0,
      "text": "when there is no problem in view --"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 106849.0,
      "end_time": 110376.0,
      "text": "especially when there is no problem in view."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 111263.0,
      "end_time": 116415.0,
      "text": "We must seek to know as much of what there is to know of all things,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 116439.0,
      "end_time": 120717.0,
      "text": "limited only by the insufficiency of our human nature,"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 120742.0,
      "end_time": 123286.0,
      "text": "and not only when the need arises."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 124534.0,
      "end_time": 128649.0,
      "text": "Those who do not seek knowledge when it is not needed"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 129561.0,
      "end_time": 133139.0,
      "text": "will not have it when they must have it."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 134777.0,
      "end_time": 138872.0,
      "text": "The biggest crisis in Africa today is the crisis of knowledge:"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 138896.0,
      "end_time": 140916.0,
      "text": "how to produce it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 140940.0,
      "end_time": 142571.0,
      "text": "how to manage it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 142595.0,
      "end_time": 145303.0,
      "text": "and how to deploy it effectively."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 146421.0,
      "end_time": 150474.0,
      "text": "For instance, Africa does not have a water crisis."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 151284.0,
      "end_time": 154218.0,
      "text": "It has a knowledge crisis regarding its water,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 155251.0,
      "end_time": 157738.0,
      "text": "where and what types it is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 157762.0,
      "end_time": 163766.0,
      "text": "how it can be tapped and made available where and when needed to all and sundry."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 165144.0,
      "end_time": 167803.0,
      "text": "How does a continent that is home"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 167827.0,
      "end_time": 170891.0,
      "text": "to some of the largest bodies of water in the world --"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 171708.0,
      "end_time": 173260.0,
      "text": "the Nile,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 173587.0,
      "end_time": 174828.0,
      "text": "the Niger,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 175291.0,
      "end_time": 176676.0,
      "text": "the Congo,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 176700.0,
      "end_time": 178250.0,
      "text": "the Zambezi"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 178274.0,
      "end_time": 179898.0,
      "text": "and the Orange Rivers --"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 180553.0,
      "end_time": 182996.0,
      "text": "be said to have a water crisis,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 183200.0,
      "end_time": 185670.0,
      "text": "including in countries"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 185910.0,
      "end_time": 186733.0,
      "text": "where those rivers are?"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 188387.0,
      "end_time": 190308.0,
      "text": "And that is only surface water."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 191450.0,
      "end_time": 195600.0,
      "text": "While we wrongly dissipate our energies fighting the wrong crises,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 195300.0,
      "end_time": 197712.0,
      "text": "all those who invest in knowledge about us"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 197736.0,
      "end_time": 202760.0,
      "text": "are busy figuring out how to pipe water from Libya&#39;s aquifers"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 203458.0,
      "end_time": 205728.0,
      "text": "to quench Europe&#39;s thirst."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 206811.0,
      "end_time": 209184.0,
      "text": "Such is our knowledge of our water resources"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 209208.0,
      "end_time": 211340.0,
      "text": "that many of our countries have given up"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 211364.0,
      "end_time": 214101.0,
      "text": "on making potable water a routine presence"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 214125.0,
      "end_time": 215884.0,
      "text": "in the lives of Africans,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 215908.0,
      "end_time": 217563.0,
      "text": "rich or poor,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 217587.0,
      "end_time": 219420.0,
      "text": "high and low,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 219660.0,
      "end_time": 220496.0,
      "text": "rural and urban."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 221252.0,
      "end_time": 224722.0,
      "text": "We eagerly accept what the merchants of misery"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 224746.0,
      "end_time": 228269.0,
      "text": "and the global African Studies safari professoriat"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 228293.0,
      "end_time": 230249.0,
      "text": "and their aid-addled,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 230273.0,
      "end_time": 233122.0,
      "text": "autonomy-fearing African minions"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 233146.0,
      "end_time": 236384.0,
      "text": "in government, universities and civil society"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 236408.0,
      "end_time": 240543.0,
      "text": "tell us regarding how nature has been to stinting towards Africa"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 240568.0,
      "end_time": 244344.0,
      "text": "when it comes to the distribution of water resources in the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 244947.0,
      "end_time": 248703.0,
      "text": "We are content to run our cities and rural dwellings alike"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 248727.0,
      "end_time": 250101.0,
      "text": "on boreholes."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 252213.0,
      "end_time": 256618.0,
      "text": "How does one run metropolises on boreholes and wells?"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 259550.0,
      "end_time": 261990.0,
      "text": "Does Africa have a food crisis?"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 261861.0,
      "end_time": 264313.0,
      "text": "Again, the answer is no."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 265429.0,
      "end_time": 270655.0,
      "text": "It is yet another knowledge crisis regarding Africa&#39;s agricultural resources,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 270680.0,
      "end_time": 272700.0,
      "text": "what and where they are,"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 272724.0,
      "end_time": 277236.0,
      "text": "and how they can be best managed to make Africans live more lives"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 277261.0,
      "end_time": 278610.0,
      "text": "that are worth living."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 279907.0,
      "end_time": 282255.0,
      "text": "Otherwise, how does one explain the fact"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 282279.0,
      "end_time": 285545.0,
      "text": "that geography puts the source of the River Nile in Ethiopia,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 286572.0,
      "end_time": 289964.0,
      "text": "and its people cannot have water for their lives?"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 290736.0,
      "end_time": 294616.0,
      "text": "And the same geography puts California in the desert,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 294641.0,
      "end_time": 296312.0,
      "text": "but it is a breadbasket."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 297578.0,
      "end_time": 300407.0,
      "text": "The difference, obviously, is not geography."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 301413.0,
      "end_time": 302742.0,
      "text": "It is knowledge."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 303686.0,
      "end_time": 305678.0,
      "text": "Colorado&#39;s aquifers"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 305702.0,
      "end_time": 307842.0,
      "text": "grow California&#39;s pistachios."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 308900.0,
      "end_time": 311780.0,
      "text": "Why can&#39;t Libya&#39;s aquifers"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 311102.0,
      "end_time": 313729.0,
      "text": "grow sorghum in northern Nigeria?"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 314882.0,
      "end_time": 317715.0,
      "text": "Why does Nigeria not aspire"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 317739.0,
      "end_time": 319143.0,
      "text": "to feed the world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 319866.0,
      "end_time": 321940.0,
      "text": "not just itself?"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 321797.0,
      "end_time": 325628.0,
      "text": "If Africa&#39;s land is so poor, as we are often told,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 325652.0,
      "end_time": 327860.0,
      "text": "why are outsiders,"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 327884.0,
      "end_time": 332490.0,
      "text": "from the United Arab Emirates all the way to South Korea,"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 332730.0,
      "end_time": 335325.0,
      "text": "buying up vast acreages of our land,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 335349.0,
      "end_time": 337517.0,
      "text": "to grow food, no less,"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 337541.0,
      "end_time": 339238.0,
      "text": "to feed their people"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 339262.0,
      "end_time": 342884.0,
      "text": "in lands that are truly more geographically stinting?"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 343958.0,
      "end_time": 347296.0,
      "text": "The new landowners are not planning to import new topsoil"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 347320.0,
      "end_time": 350222.0,
      "text": "to make their African acquisitions more arable."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 350246.0,
      "end_time": 355219.0,
      "text": "Again, a singular instance of knowledge deficiency."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 356990.0,
      "end_time": 358604.0,
      "text": "In the 19th century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 359430.0,
      "end_time": 360890.0,
      "text": "our predecessors,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 360914.0,
      "end_time": 364258.0,
      "text": "just years removed from the ravages of slavery and the slave trade,"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 365837.0,
      "end_time": 369270.0,
      "text": "were exploring the Niger and Congo Rivers"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 369520.0,
      "end_time": 373101.0,
      "text": "with a view to turning Africa&#39;s resources to the advantage of its people"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 373125.0,
      "end_time": 375190.0,
      "text": "and to the rest of humanity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 375513.0,
      "end_time": 379616.0,
      "text": "and their 20th-century successors were dreaming of harnessing"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 379640.0,
      "end_time": 381848.0,
      "text": "the powers of the River Congo"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 381872.0,
      "end_time": 383820.0,
      "text": "to light up the whole continent."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 384642.0,
      "end_time": 388780.0,
      "text": "Now only buccaneer capitalists from Europe"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 388102.0,
      "end_time": 390477.0,
      "text": "are scheming of doing the same,"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 390502.0,
      "end_time": 394140.0,
      "text": "but for exports to Europe and South Africa."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 394736.0,
      "end_time": 396380.0,
      "text": "And they are even suggesting"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 396404.0,
      "end_time": 398990.0,
      "text": "that Congolese may not benefit from this scheme,"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 399140.0,
      "end_time": 403500.0,
      "text": "because, according to them, Congolese communities are too small"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 403290.0,
      "end_time": 405568.0,
      "text": "to make providing them with electricity"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 406123.0,
      "end_time": 408336.0,
      "text": "a viable concern."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 410174.0,
      "end_time": 411953.0,
      "text": "The solution?"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 411977.0,
      "end_time": 414921.0,
      "text": "Africa must become a knowledge society,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 414945.0,
      "end_time": 418110.0,
      "text": "a defining characteristic of the modern age."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 418866.0,
      "end_time": 424175.0,
      "text": "We neither are, nor are we on the path to becoming,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 424199.0,
      "end_time": 425661.0,
      "text": "a knowledge society."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 427100.0,
      "end_time": 429220.0,
      "text": "Things have not always been this way"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 430696.0,
      "end_time": 433631.0,
      "text": "when it comes to knowledge production and Africa."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 433655.0,
      "end_time": 438731.0,
      "text": "In antiquity, the world went to Africa for intellectual enrichment."
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 439339.0,
      "end_time": 442458.0,
      "text": "There were celebrated centers of learning,"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 442482.0,
      "end_time": 446562.0,
      "text": "attracting questers from all parts of the then-known world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 446586.0,
      "end_time": 448981.0,
      "text": "seeking knowledge about that world."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 449804.0,
      "end_time": 453438.0,
      "text": "What happened then has implications for our present."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 453968.0,
      "end_time": 455786.0,
      "text": "For example,"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 455810.0,
      "end_time": 462476.0,
      "text": "how Roman Africa managed the relationship between settlers and natives"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 462500.0,
      "end_time": 466920.0,
      "text": "between the second and fourth centuries of our era"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 466116.0,
      "end_time": 469108.0,
      "text": "might have something to teach us when it comes to confronting"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 469132.0,
      "end_time": 472540.0,
      "text": "not-too-dissimilar problems at the present time."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 473345.0,
      "end_time": 477115.0,
      "text": "But how many classics departments do we have in our universities?"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 478423.0,
      "end_time": 480946.0,
      "text": "Because we do not invest in knowledge,"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 480970.0,
      "end_time": 483270.0,
      "text": "people come to Africa now"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 483510.0,
      "end_time": 485577.0,
      "text": "not as a place of intellectual enrichment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 486171.0,
      "end_time": 490507.0,
      "text": "but as a place where they sate their thirst for exotica."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 492538.0,
      "end_time": 494982.0,
      "text": "Yet for the last half-millennium,"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 495544.0,
      "end_time": 499320.0,
      "text": "Africa has been hemorrhaging and exporting knowledge"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 499570.0,
      "end_time": 500464.0,
      "text": "to the rest of the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 501273.0,
      "end_time": 505962.0,
      "text": "Regardless of the popular description of it as a trade in bodies,"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 505986.0,
      "end_time": 509763.0,
      "text": "the European trans-Atlantic slave trade and slavery"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 509787.0,
      "end_time": 513207.0,
      "text": "was one of the most radical and longest programs"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 513232.0,
      "end_time": 515771.0,
      "text": "of African brains export in history."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 516831.0,
      "end_time": 521247.0,
      "text": "American slave owners may have pretended that Africans were mere brutes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 521929.0,
      "end_time": 523573.0,
      "text": "beasts of burden,"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 523597.0,
      "end_time": 527542.0,
      "text": "almost as inert and dumb as other farm implements"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 527566.0,
      "end_time": 530422.0,
      "text": "they classified them with in their ledgers."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 531520.0,
      "end_time": 532361.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s what they did."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 533990.0,
      "end_time": 535539.0,
      "text": "The enslaved Africans, on the other hand,"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 535563.0,
      "end_time": 538635.0,
      "text": "knew their were embodiments of knowledge."
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 538659.0,
      "end_time": 541199.0,
      "text": "They were smiths, they were poets,"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 541223.0,
      "end_time": 544545.0,
      "text": "they were political counselors, they were princes and princesses,"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 544570.0,
      "end_time": 547261.0,
      "text": "they were mythologists, they were herbologists,"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 549689.0,
      "end_time": 551182.0,
      "text": "they were chefs."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 551206.0,
      "end_time": 552659.0,
      "text": "The list is endless."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 553367.0,
      "end_time": 555861.0,
      "text": "They, to take a single example,"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 555885.0,
      "end_time": 558881.0,
      "text": "brought the knowledge of rice cultivation"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 558905.0,
      "end_time": 560395.0,
      "text": "to the American South."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 562101.0,
      "end_time": 566576.0,
      "text": "They created some of the most original civilizational elements"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 566600.0,
      "end_time": 569442.0,
      "text": "for which the United States is now celebrated."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 570237.0,
      "end_time": 573337.0,
      "text": "They deployed their knowledge, for the most part,"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 573361.0,
      "end_time": 574881.0,
      "text": "without compensation."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 575867.0,
      "end_time": 579375.0,
      "text": "For the last half-millennium, beginning with the slave trade,"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 579399.0,
      "end_time": 582450.0,
      "text": "Africa has been exporting brains"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 582690.0,
      "end_time": 586790.0,
      "text": "while simultaneously breaking the chains of knowledge transmission"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 586815.0,
      "end_time": 588545.0,
      "text": "on the continent itself,"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 588569.0,
      "end_time": 592716.0,
      "text": "with dire consequences for the systems of knowledge production in Africa."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 593664.0,
      "end_time": 598234.0,
      "text": "Successive generations are cut off from the intellectual production"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 598258.0,
      "end_time": 599475.0,
      "text": "of their predecessors."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 600363.0,
      "end_time": 603406.0,
      "text": "We keep producing for external markets"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 603430.0,
      "end_time": 606465.0,
      "text": "while beggaring our own internal needs."
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 607411.0,
      "end_time": 608738.0,
      "text": "At present,"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 608763.0,
      "end_time": 611366.0,
      "text": "much of the best knowledge about Africa"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 611390.0,
      "end_time": 614698.0,
      "text": "is neither produced nor housed there,"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 614722.0,
      "end_time": 617795.0,
      "text": "even when it is produced by Africans."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 618634.0,
      "end_time": 621950.0,
      "text": "Because we are dominated by immediate needs"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 621119.0,
      "end_time": 624626.0,
      "text": "and relevant solutions when it comes to what we should know,"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 624650.0,
      "end_time": 627175.0,
      "text": "we are happy to hand over to others"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 627199.0,
      "end_time": 629659.0,
      "text": "the responsibility to produce knowledge,"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 629683.0,
      "end_time": 633961.0,
      "text": "including knowledge about, of and for us,"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 633985.0,
      "end_time": 636250.0,
      "text": "and to do so far away from us."
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 636853.0,
      "end_time": 639996.0,
      "text": "We are ever eager to consume knowledge"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 640200.0,
      "end_time": 642419.0,
      "text": "and have but a mere portion of it"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 642443.0,
      "end_time": 646620.0,
      "text": "without any anxiety about ownership and location."
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 647707.0,
      "end_time": 651310.0,
      "text": "African universities are now all too content"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 651334.0,
      "end_time": 654859.0,
      "text": "to have e-connections with libraries elsewhere,"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 654884.0,
      "end_time": 657758.0,
      "text": "having given up ambitions on building libraries"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 657782.0,
      "end_time": 661473.0,
      "text": "to which the world would come for intellectual edification."
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 662411.0,
      "end_time": 666608.0,
      "text": "Control over who decides what should be stocked on our shelves"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 666633.0,
      "end_time": 670273.0,
      "text": "and how access to collections should be determined"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 670297.0,
      "end_time": 674128.0,
      "text": "are made to rest on our trust in our partners&#39; good faith"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 674152.0,
      "end_time": 676884.0,
      "text": "that they will not abandon us down the road."
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 677981.0,
      "end_time": 680170.0,
      "text": "This must change."
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 681930.0,
      "end_time": 684613.0,
      "text": "Africa must become a place of knowledge again."
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 685433.0,
      "end_time": 690318.0,
      "text": "Knowledge production actually expands the economy."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 691262.0,
      "end_time": 694337.0,
      "text": "Take archaeological digs, for instance,"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 694361.0,
      "end_time": 696516.0,
      "text": "and their impact on tourism."
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 697527.0,
      "end_time": 700907.0,
      "text": "Our desires to unearth our antiquity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 700931.0,
      "end_time": 705704.0,
      "text": "especially those remote times of which we have no written records,"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 705728.0,
      "end_time": 710742.0,
      "text": "requires investment in archaeology and related disciplines,"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 710766.0,
      "end_time": 712954.0,
      "text": "e.g., paleoanthropology."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 713715.0,
      "end_time": 717533.0,
      "text": "Yet, although it is our past we seek to know,"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 717557.0,
      "end_time": 719279.0,
      "text": "by sheer serendipity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 719935.0,
      "end_time": 723800.0,
      "text": "archaeology may shed light on the global human experience"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 723824.0,
      "end_time": 725987.0,
      "text": "and yield economic payoffs"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 726110.0,
      "end_time": 729247.0,
      "text": "that were no part of the original reasons for digging."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 730969.0,
      "end_time": 736916.0,
      "text": "We must find a way to make knowledge and its production sexy and rewarding;"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 737985.0,
      "end_time": 740933.0,
      "text": "rewarding, not in the crass sense of moneymaking"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 741600.0,
      "end_time": 746526.0,
      "text": "but in terms of making it worthwhile to indulge in the pursuit of knowledge,"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 747101.0,
      "end_time": 748495.0,
      "text": "support the existence"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 748519.0,
      "end_time": 751696.0,
      "text": "of knowledge-producing groups and intellectuals,"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 751720.0,
      "end_time": 753895.0,
      "text": "ensuring that the continent"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 755499.0,
      "end_time": 758705.0,
      "text": "becomes the immediate locus of knowledge production,"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 758729.0,
      "end_time": 760662.0,
      "text": "distribution and consumption,"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 761385.0,
      "end_time": 763880.0,
      "text": "and that instead of having its depositories"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 763904.0,
      "end_time": 765897.0,
      "text": "beyond Africa&#39;s boundaries,"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 765921.0,
      "end_time": 769184.0,
      "text": "people once more come from the rest of the world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 769706.0,
      "end_time": 773175.0,
      "text": "even if in virtual space, to learn from us."
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 774370.0,
      "end_time": 779911.0,
      "text": "All this we do as custodians on behalf of common humanity."
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 782157.0,
      "end_time": 784731.0,
      "text": "Creating a knowledge society in Africa,"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 785501.0,
      "end_time": 791430.0,
      "text": "for me, would be one way to celebrate and simultaneously enhance diversity"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 791454.0,
      "end_time": 796308.0,
      "text": "by infinitely enriching it with material and additional artifacts --"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 796887.0,
      "end_time": 798996.0,
      "text": "artifacts that we furnish"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 799200.0,
      "end_time": 800995.0,
      "text": "by our strivings"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 801190.0,
      "end_time": 802432.0,
      "text": "in the knowledge field."
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 803470.0,
      "end_time": 804453.0,
      "text": "Thank you very much."
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 804477.0,
      "end_time": 808269.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}